Agenda:
Conditional statements/Decision making statements
if
if else
if else if
switch
==>Conditional/Decision statement<==
It gives the power to take decision when to execute and what to be done if condition true
Example:
1.Fetch the database record of database connection successful
2. Run test case if bowser does not equals to null
3. Fetch records if excel file exist

if(Boolean_expression1)
{
//Execute if the boolean expression 1 is true
}
else if(Boolean_expression2)
{
//Execute if the boolean expression 2 is true
}
else if(Boolean_expression3)
{
//Execute if the boolean expression 3 is true
}
else 
{
//Execute when non of the above condition is true
}


Switch:

=> It allows you match with multiple cases
switch(expression)
{
case value:
//code here
break;
case value:
//code here
break;
//you can have any number of case statements.

default:
}

=>Data type should be same for comparison
=>We can have multiple cases
=> we can use only Integers String and Enums
=>Break is optional but if not provided it will check all cases till the end
=>Default is optional





